/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14623.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: pierce and blunt?</span><hr size=1> It doesn't take much time at all to raise a skill from 0 to 225, so I wouldn't go out of my way to raise skills for which I don't have decent weapons. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uhathelsay.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hathelsay</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 77<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/25/02 6:54:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14623.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: pierce and blunt?</span><hr size=1> Spend the extra time now keeping weapon skills up. I learned the hard way(after disregarding posts like this one) and had to grunt my way through getting peircing up from 1 at 54th level. Trust me..keep them up now. It's much easier to get 5 points a level than getting 212. <p><table border="0" width=300><tr><td><font size=2 Face=Arial><img src="http://eq.metasystemsinc.com/images/hath_sol_sig.jpg"><br>Hathelsay Ionythe<br>Cavalier of Mithaniel Marr<br><a href="http://www.keldar.com" target="_blank">Dragons of Kel'Dar</a><br>Xegony</font></td></tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uwhitchywhon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Whitchywhon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 71<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/25/02 7:53:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14623.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: pierce and blunt?</span><hr size=1> Ok, so whitch do I work on?<br>besides 1hs, and 2hs?<br>1hp ? <br>Is it the same as 2hp?<br><br>Lances are 2hp, no?<br><br>1hb &amp; 2hb don't seem like a Paladin type weapon to me.<br><br>Aren't most of the better weapons pots lvl 45 either 1hs, 2hs or 2hp like the lances?<br><br>Chipp <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uhathelsay.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hathelsay</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 79<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/25/02 7:59:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14623.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: pierce and blunt?</span><hr size=1> You are correct about peircing. 1hp and 2hp use the same skill. And there are lots of good weapons for all skills. 1hs 2hs 2hp 1hb 2hb. Take your pick <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><table border="0" width=300><tr><td><font size=2 Face=Arial><img src="http://eq.metasystemsinc.com/images/hath_sol_sig.jpg"><br>Hathelsay Ionythe<br>Cavalier of Mithaniel Marr<br><a href="http://www.keldar.com" target="_blank">Dragons of Kel'Dar</a><br>Xegony</font></td></tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dyermaker>Dyermaker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 57<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/25/02 8:00:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14623.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: pierce and blunt?</span><hr size=1> Here's the reason to work on those skills...  there are a lot of people who make the same assumptions as you, and only work on the 1HS and 2HS skills. By the time you're in your 30's, equal or better Blunt weapons will be available for a lot less cost. Demand is less, cost comes down. If you happen to be one of the few who uses these skills, or at least keeps them on par with your others, then you will benefit.<br><br>Personally I use whatever weapon will give me the most damage per second, and since I don't know what will fall into my lap tomorrow, I try to keep them all as high as possible. I do admit that 2HS and 2HP are the only ones maxed for my level though...<br><br><br><br> <p>Dyermaker Merdinho -- The Lost Paladin and Lil'Bastard<BR>40 Paladin of Tunare, Quellious Server<BR>Profiles: <A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=32626">Magelo<A> -- <A HREF="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/userinfo.html?char=16712">Allakhazam</A> --<A HREF="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=3366">Caster's Realm</A><BR>Lil'Bastard Clan: <A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=32626">Dyermaker</A> | <A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=91012">Chapado</A> | Chiad  | <A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=82578">Malvado</A> | <A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=92554">Narnya</A> | Solyony <BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usorrun.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sorrun</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/25/02 8:40:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14623.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: pierce and blunt?</span><hr size=1> Keeping all skills maxed will do nothing but help you in the long run... <br><br>I wouldnt go out of my way to build everything to max.. for instance, 2hb has alot less good weapons then 1hs, 2hs, 1hb and pierce but those 4 are a good idea to try and keep at least close to maxed.  If you get a decent 2hb weapon then what the heck, but I would only work on 2hb after the others are maxed. <p><table border="0">  <tr>    <td></td>    <td valign="center" >    <font face="Times New Roman" color=#006600 size=2>      <p style="MARGIN-TOP: 1px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 1px" align=left><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=101187" target="_blank">Sorrun MacGregor</a> - 52 druid</p>      <p style="MARGIN-TOP: 1px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 1px" align=left><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=101326" target="_blank">Ferynn MacGregor</a> - 27 enchanter</p>      <p style="MARGIN-TOP: 1px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 1px" align=left><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=101273" target="_blank">Hartos MacGregor</a> - 30 paladin</p>      <p style="MARGIN-TOP: 1px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 1px" align=left><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=101327" target="_blank">Brikwaul MacGregor</a> - 20 warrior</p>      <p style="MARGIN-TOP: 12px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 1px" align=center>Clan MacGregor - Officer</p>      <p style="MARGIN-TOP: 6px; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 1px" align=center>Bristlebane</p>    </font>    </td>  </tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uwhitchywhon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Whitchywhon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 74<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/25/02 8:45:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14623.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: pierce and blunt?</span><hr size=1> Thanks y'all<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udigrenkaellise.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DigrenKaellise</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 75<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/25/02 8:47:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14623.topic&index=8>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: pierce and blunt?</span><hr size=1> <br>I have 1HS, 2HS, and pierce maxed.  The only weapons I use are piercing (99%) and 2HS (1%).  The problem is, my best 1-handed weapon in my watersprinkler from hate, a blunt weapon.  If I did want to use a shield for some reason (resists, bashes), I would have to go back down to my ghoulbane for 1HS. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=43978">Digren Kaellise</a><br>Cavalier 3 of Tunare<br><a href="http://www.childrenofthephoenix.org">< Children of the Phoenix ></a><br><a href="http://www.tunareguildalliance.org/">Tunare Guild Alliance</a><br></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujcasetn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>jcasetn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/25/02 8:56:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14623.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: pierce and blunt?</span><hr size=1> My take: Keep 1hs, 2hs and piercing up.  It's true there are some nice blunt weapons in the game but they are extremely rare.  If you get one, fine, grunt your way to maxing it.<br><br>For piercing, at low levels you can get a MOTQ, which nowadays goes for 50-100p.  Or, if you can afford it, go for a Centi WS, which I've seen on several occasions going for as low as 200p.  After that there are some super high level piercing weapons like great spear of dawn.  There aren't a ton of peircers out there but there are enough that it makes it worth it to keep the skill up. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usamin1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Samin1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/25/02 9:14:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14623.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: pierce and blunt?</span><hr size=1> 2HB is a great skill to keep, all through my levels I was able to get great 2HB wepons cheap, because no one else would use them.  At level 49 I bought a Granite Face Grinder (2hb 29 36 10 str wis int) for about 2k (which at the time was an amazing deal).  The guy I bought it from said he had been trying to sell it for 5 days straight with no tells.  With Vellious came lots of better 2hp and 2hs weps from DN and ToV, but you can still find 2hb wepons very cheap. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubizomb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bizomb</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 636<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/25/02 9:25:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14623.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: pierce and blunt?</span><hr size=1> Yup, Keep em all maxed.<br>It's not that difficult to get your skill up later on, but it still can be annoying. It probably took me a week a piece in L54-56 raising piercing and 2HB because I had not worked on those skills earlier on. I also had about 80% haste consistantly and boon of the garou up with +100dex so raising skills went alot faster than it would normally. That's going from zero skill to 215ish.<br>There are lots of weapons in all categories for you to choose from. Don't limit yourself by what skills you have maxed. <br>Now I have all skills except for 1HB maxed. So I don't have an issue picking up pretty much any weapon. <br><br>However, on the same token I wouldn't go out of my way to buy a crappy weapon just to build the skill up, but if  you can come across something reasonably quick and cheap then I would say go for it. It'll benefit you in the long run. <br><br><br>Biz. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uboleslav.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Boleslav</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/25/02 9:56:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14623.topic&index=12>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: pierce and blunt?</span><hr size=1> Dwarven Sap (8/20) is a nice weapon at 28.  I still use mine occasionally at 49 when I am tanking casting mobs in a group.  The low delay puts a lot of hits on the mob and keeps me up on the aggro list and the .4 ratio isn't too bad either.  I vote for working your 1HB up and suspect you will find a place in your repertoire for the Dwarven Sap.<br><br>Boleslav Forgehammer<br>Paladin of Brell in his 49th Campaign<br>E'Ci - Destiny Awaits<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukidkod1ak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kidkod1ak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 94<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/25/02 10:03:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14623.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: pierce and blunt?</span><hr size=1> Working on your skills at the least cant hurt. In the end you may be happy. For instance my first Hate raid produced a Dark Metal Holy Water Sprinkler 16/29 1hb. I sure was glad I had worked my 1hb up and could use it right away. <p><center><bold><font color="green" size = 5><a href = "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=101014">Varner Rapscallion</a> </font><br>57 Knight of Brell<br>--Raiders of Chaos--</bold></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugloynholyforge.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gloyn Holyforge</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Administrator</span><br>  Posts: 51<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/25/02 10:17:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14623.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: pierce and blunt?</span><hr size=1> I've always been careful keep my weapons skills up.  At lower levels...dwarven sap and BIBS.  Now at upper levels, GFG and Carved Dragonbone Spear.  There are plenty of good 1hb's but normally we don't use them because they are considered &quot;warrior weapons or monk weapons.&quot; You need to find the weapon that is good for you and will work for whatever group you are doing. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugloynholyforge.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gloyn Holyforge</A> at: 3/3/02 10:37:09 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udisavowedknight.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Disavowed Knight</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/25/02 5:37:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14623.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: pierce and blunt?</span><hr size=1> Just a few words on raiseing weapon skills.<br><br>My 2hs was pathetic about a 127.  I went to Vek and grouped with a shamy and got str 255 and dex darn close and hasted by a enchanter.  I went up to about 180ish that day.  The next day I went back and maxed my skill out.  All in all about 100point raise in a day and a half of full exp grind.  Remember the higher your level the higher levels of your average group and there for the better the buffs.  i.e. It doesn't take long to raise a skill in the post 50 era.  I'd imagine I could spend two weeks and raise all my weapon proficencies up to max.  But i like my current weapons and rather exp grind then chase down new toys.  If I get a great 2hp or 2hb better then my current toys will I train up?  yup but not til then.  Not when it's soo easy.<br><br>stay safe all<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=barellron>Barellron</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/25/02 6:13:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14623.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: pierce and blunt?</span><hr size=1> Well, this may just be due to the fact that I'm a packrat, but I believe that all weapon skills are useful at some point in time.<br><br>It really isn't that bad.  I used 1hs solely until about 20 (this was a long time ago, you didn't carry two weapons because that Combine Long Sword was all you could afford =p).  I got ahold of a Deepwater Harpoon around then, and tried to keep both skills up, but the 30pp payoff for that onehander was too tempting =p.  I used 2hs pretty much all the way to the mid 40s... and I regretted it.  To make a long story short, I kept running into different useful weapons as I went up.  But I was crap for a tank while I was working on these skills.  It's nice to have them all at a useable level now.  The weapon choices are amazing, and I can use multiple things situationally.<br><br>So, yeah, you don't have to work on them right away, but don't neglect them all together.  The mid and high-end game is filled with great weapons of multiple skill-types. <p><img src="http://www.strike9.com/eq/file.aspx/path=/Barellron/fullsize/Triump+Sig+Smaller+Short.jpg" border="0"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap w